    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1475"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1475">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/214.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Bonney</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San Luis Potosí</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 23, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Military commandant here, Colonel Borboa, threatening foreigners with forced loan
                    and threatening to take possession American and foreign mines here within five
                    days. Will you please address highest authority to restrain this officer.
                    Railroad service south and east has been suspended.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bonney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
